      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-1 col-sm-12">
        <img class="img-responsive" src="/img/v2/activate.png" alt="">
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-5 col-sm-12">
        <p class="lead">Alternatively, you can activate Alpheios from the browser's context menu.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-1 col-sm-12">
        <img class="img-responsive" src="/img/v2/activate2.png" alt="">
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-5 col-sm-12">
        <p class="lead">The Alpheios panel will open. This panel contains instructions for accessing the word lookup functionality that Alpheios adds to the browser pages on which you activate it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-1 col-sm-12">
        <img class="img-responsive" src="/img/v2/panel.png" alt="">
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-5 col-sm-12">
        <p class="lead">If you close this panel, you can always reopen it via the <b>Info</b> entry in the <b>Alpheios Reading Tools</b> submenu in browser's context menu or via <thead>
          <b>Define</b> or <b>Inflect</b> options in the Alpheios popup.
        </p>
      </div>
